Genetically engineered Marines travel throughout Space, battling depraved heretics, dishonourable traitors, and vile aliens.

This set includes 4 powered gauntlets, two holding the torn off heads of two different types of alien beast - a brutal ork, and a sinister soulstealer. The third holds a retro style space beaky helmet, and the fourth is empty, perhaps for you to add in your own head model! All four have supported versions.

This is an updated version of the first thing I ever tried to 'sculpt', as opposed to arrange geometric shapes - an ork head. It's a little reflection on my part, comparing where I started to where I am. It's been a slow process, as I take what digital hobby time I can in between physical modelling and all my other fickle interests! But it's still nice to see what I feel in some improvement.

You can see the original here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/power-gauntlet-prime-scale-powered-gauntlet-holding-head

I am an amateur enthusiast 3D designer, and appreciate all constructive feedback. Please check out my other designs for more wargame models, and please consider following me, posting a make, or even leaving a donation via my profile!

A few more Neo-Retro super soldiers. This set includes a heavy machine gun, a shoulder mounted laser cannon, two leader with capes and different weapon options, an alternate plasma gun pose, and 2 alternate rifleman poses. These are my own sculpts (no remixing).

I've included 2 sizes. My usual "15mm" size are about 18.5mm at the eye, 20mm at the top of the head (they are intended to be bigger than normal 15mm humans). I made the 28mm size comparable to classic sculpts. If you want them closer to the size of new space marines you can always just scale them up a bit more.

*I currently ONLY have pre-supported files for the 15mm ones. All supported models have been test printed. I tend to go heavier on the supports. I recommend using the hot water method to remove them.

OK, just a scooped, supported and magnet ready version of Wolfkeeper's GRIMDARK MINUTE FLYING ARMED TRANSPORT and nitramthx's burning little dino for galactic crusaders. They are great little free files and will work well at 8mm. I sized them to have roughly a 70mm wingspan, but size however you like, just be cognicent that resizing circles can make ovals.

I removed the lower floor of the model, so the magent insert is on the roof of the model and can accept magnets up to 10mm - so pick your poison.

I also did some editing to make sure there were no resin captures.

These models are not hollowed in the traditional sense - no resin can be captured and all internals can be exposed to UV light for curing. Some idiot will not look at the files and mis-understand that and will invariably do an "aktuallly blah blah blah" - it always seems to happen....
